Edwsy Nnachi, Abakaliki Governor David Umahi of Ebonyi State has provided two Coaster buses and 10 Hilux vans to convey travellers and visitors from the state to Sam Mbakwe Airport, Owerri to minimise their inconvenience. The Akanu Ibiam International Airport, Enugu, had been temporarily shut by the Federal Airport Authority of Nigeria for repairs, among others. The Special Assistant to the Governor on New Media, Francis Nweze, in a statement made available to journalists in Abakaliki, on Wednesday, said the gesture was in fulfilment of Umahi’s promise to alleviate the difficulties and security challenges travellers and visitors in the state faced due to the temporary closure of Enugu airport. The statement read, “Governor Umahi has directed the provision of two Coaster buses, 10 security Hilux vehicles, conducive shuttle lodges in Abakaliki and Owerri, and traveller care phone lines.” Copyright PUNCH.
